    "This is consistent with observations for Spanner [6], Bigtable [3], and CockroachDB [4].",
    "C. Coordination LatencyCoordination cost increases with cluster size due to consensus protocols, global timestamps, metadata synchronization, and topology changes.",
    "We model coordination latency as:L coord (H) = η log H + µH θ,where 0 < θ < 1 creates a super-logarithmic but sub-linear growth curve, matching empirical measurements in distributed consensus literature [2].",
    "D. Total LatencyWe define:L(H, V) = L node (V) + L coord (H).",
    "This implies:∂L ∂H > 0 and ∂L ∂∥V ∥ < 0."
